The Golden State Warriors once again came back from a sizable deficit when it mattered the most as they leveled the NBA finals against the Toronto Raptors on Sunday night. Golden State were trailing by 11 points towards the end of the second quarter, and it looked like they were set to go 2-0 down in the NBA finals. However, they went on an 18-0 scoring run at the start of the second-half as the Raptors dried up. Toronto fought back towards the end of the game but the Warriors held on for a crucial victory to level the series at 1-1. The Warriors now have home-court advantage for the next two games. Game 3 is on Wednesday night in Oakland. Full report to follow â€¦